ANTIMONY OXIDE STORAGE 
AND HANDLING  
 

During 
handling, protective clothing and NIOSH/MSHA 
approved 
respiratory equipment should be worn. Dust control systems should be used 
throughout the handling areas. Sweeping should be avoided; a vacuum cleaner 
should be used to handle spillage. Food and cigarettes should not be taken into 
work areas. Hands and faces should be washed before smoking, eating, or 
drinking. All plant personnel should shower and change clothes before leaving 
the plant. Work clothes should be washed frequently.  

Handling and storage should be engineered to 
minimize spillage. Additionally, antimony oxide should not be stored near an 
acid, because the mixing of antimony oxide with an acid will generate stibine 
gas (HSb), a deadly poison. An MSDS sheet is available upon request. 

 

PACKING IS AVAILABLE AS FOLLOWS:

50lb bag, 40 per pallet

25kg bag, 40 per pallet

2000 poung bulk bag on pallet

Metric tonne bulk bag on pallet

Bulk Truck Loads, up to 48,000 pounds

Other packing sizes are available on a price to be 
determined basis.
 
 
 
 

 










