            Founded in 1964, United States Antimony Corporation is engaged in the exploration, development and production of antimony. The company produces sodium antimonate, antimony metal and antimony pentoxide. Its varieties of antimony products are used as fining agents, degassers and decolorizers in the production of glass. In addition, the product is used for its flame retardant applications in the production of plastics, paints, fiberglass resins and various textiles. The company also owns a controlling interest in Bear River Zeolite Company, which undertakes the mining and distribution of zeolite. The company has sales representation through various independent companies located throughout the United States. United States Antimony Corporation is headquartered in Thompson Falls, Mont.
          






















